<subSubSection id="E3D165580067511BC8EEDF463E23CFE5" pageId="1" pageNumber="241" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="AB7436D30067511BC8EEDF463E23CFE5" blockId="1.[151,1437,1374,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC10067511BC8EEDF463D2DCF08" bold="true" box="[199,334,1590,1616]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named 
<taxonomicName id="6CCB4D500067511BC99BDF473E64CF08" authorityName="Vilela &amp; Junior &amp; Furieri &amp; Lencioni" authorityYear="2021" box="[434,519,1591,1616]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="1" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeromei">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC10067511BC99BDF473E64CF08" box="[434,519,1591,1616]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">jeromei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(noun in the genitive case) after Jérôme Constant, Hemiptera expert, Direction Taxonomy and Phylogeny and collection management expert at the Royal Belgian Institute of Natural Sciences (IRSNB), for his great contributions to the odonatology, mainly working with the Selys’ collection curation and for helping us many times over the years.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E3D1655800675119C8EEDFB63C8DCBDD" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="243" pageId="1" pageNumber="241" type="description">
<paragraph id="AB7436D30067511BC8EEDFB63DBDCFB8" blockId="1.[151,1437,1374,1977]" box="[199,478,1734,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC10067511BC8EEDFB63DBDCFB8" bold="true" box="[199,478,1734,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
Description of 
<typeStatus id="747088710067511BC95EDFB63DBDCFB8" box="[375,478,1734,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">holotype</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB7436D30067511BC8EEDF9A3F8DCE14" blockId="1.[151,1437,1374,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC10067511BC8EEDF9A3D68CE5C" box="[199,267,1770,1796]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">Head.</emphasis>
Labrum, anteclypeus, postclypeus, antefrons and genae black; two brownish small D-shaped spots (on each side of lateral ocelli); a large transversal pale stripe ranging from the postocular lobes through the occipital area, slightly darker in the occipital area; remainder of the head matte black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB7436D30067511BC8EEDE263E87CEE0" blockId="1.[151,1437,1374,1977]" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC10067511BC8EEDE263D7BCE28" box="[199,280,1878,1904]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">Thorax</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="33F02A560067511BC90EDE263DE1CE28" box="[295,386,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,198,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[155,1433,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male habitus: a—dorsal view of a lectotype of Leptagrion andromache Hagen in Selys, 1876 and paratype´s labels (IRSNB); b—lateral view of L. andromache from Amapá state, Brazil; c—lateral view of holotype of Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (FAAL); d—Comparison between Leptagrion andromache and Leptagrion jeromei forewing pterostigma." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704350/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">Figs. 1c</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="33F02A560067511BC9A7DE263DB6CE28" box="[398,469,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[269,1331,193,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-17@4.[256,1331,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Male prothorax in lateral view: a—Leptagrion andromache from Amapá state, Brazil; b—Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (holotype—FAAL); male hind lobe of prothorax in dorsal view: c—Leptagrion andromache from Amapá state, Brazil; d—Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (holotype—FAAL)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704352/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="241">2b, 2c</figureCitation>
). Prothorax: anterior lobe pale brown; in dorsal view, medial lobe reddish-brown; hind lobe bluish, nearly straight at the middle, with blunt rounded corners. Pterothorax: black humeral stripe covering upper half of mesepisternum, remainder pale brown.
</paragraph>
<caption id="FFB4665B00645118C8BEDEE7389ECEA0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704350" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5704350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704350/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="242" startId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" targetBox="[172,1418,198,1909]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="AB7436D300645118C8BEDEE7389ECEA0" blockId="2.[151,1437,1943,2040]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118C8BEDEE73D70CEF7" bold="true" box="[151,275,1943,1967]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
Male habitus: 
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118C981DEE83DD6CEE8" bold="true" box="[424,437,1944,1968]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">a</emphasis>
—dorsal view of a lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="6CCB4D5000645118CAD8DEE8384ECEE8" authority="Hagen" authorityName="Hagen" box="[753,1069,1944,1968]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andromache">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118CAD8DEE83F85CEE8" box="[753,998,1944,1968]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">Leptagrion andromache</emphasis>
Hagen
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118CC1ADEE83824CEF7" box="[1075,1095,1944,1967]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">in</emphasis>
Selys, 1876 and paratype´s labels (IRSNB); 
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118C929DECC3D6DCE8C" bold="true" box="[256,270,1980,2004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">b</emphasis>
—lateral view of 
<taxonomicName id="6CCB4D5000645118C996DECC3E34CE8C" box="[447,599,1980,2004]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andromache">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118C996DECC3E34CE8C" box="[447,599,1980,2004]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">L. andromache</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Amapá state, Brazil; 
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118CB41DECC3F10CE8C" bold="true" box="[872,883,1980,2004]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">c</emphasis>
—lateral view of holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="6CCB4D5000645118CCB7DECC3902CE8B" authority="Vilela &amp; Junior &amp; Furieri &amp; Lencioni, 2021" authorityName="Vilela &amp; Junior &amp; Furieri &amp; Lencioni" authorityYear="2021" box="[1182,1377,1980,2003]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeromei" status="spec. nov.">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118CCB7DECC3902CE8B" box="[1182,1377,1980,2003]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">Leptagrion jeromei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118CD4EDECC3CA0CEA0" bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="828C57BA00645118CD4EDECC3CA0CEA0" pageId="2" pageNumber="242" rank="species">spec. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(FAAL); 
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118C901DE903D55CEA0" bold="true" box="[296,310,2016,2040]" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">d</emphasis>
—Comparison between 
<taxonomicName id="6CCB4D5000645118CA04DE903F41CEA0" box="[557,802,2016,2040]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andromache">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118CA04DE903F41CEA0" box="[557,802,2016,2040]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">Leptagrion andromache</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="6CCB4D5000645118CB7ADE903875CEAF" authorityName="Vilela &amp; Junior &amp; Furieri &amp; Lencioni" authorityYear="2021" box="[851,1046,2016,2039]" class="Insecta" family="Coenagrionidae" genus="Leptagrion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Odonata" pageId="2" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jeromei">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100645118CB7ADE903875CEAF" box="[851,1046,2016,2039]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="242">Leptagrion jeromei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
forewing pterostigma.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="AB7436D300655119C8EED9E73E8AC98D" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100655119C8EED9E73D68C9E8" box="[199,267,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Wings</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="33F02A5600655119C932D9E73D09C9E9" box="[283,362,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,198,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[155,1433,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male habitus: a—dorsal view of a lectotype of Leptagrion andromache Hagen in Selys, 1876 and paratype´s labels (IRSNB); b—lateral view of L. andromache from Amapá state, Brazil; c—lateral view of holotype of Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (FAAL); d—Comparison between Leptagrion andromache and Leptagrion jeromei forewing pterostigma." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704350/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
). Hyaline; pterostigma dark brown, rhomboid, occupying nearly one cell; 10 Px in FW, 11 Px in RHW (
<quantity id="6C339B3600655119C8C1D9CB3D42C98D" box="[232,289,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" unit="in" value="10.0">10 in</quantity>
LHW); RP2 arising at Px 
<quantity id="6C339B3600655119CA63D9CB3E16C98D" box="[586,629,187,213]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" unit="in" value="6.0">6 in</quantity>
all wings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB7436D300655119C8EED9AF3E2AC819" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100655119C8EED9AF3D52C9A1" box="[199,305,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="33F02A5600655119C96BD9AF3DF0C9A1" box="[322,403,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[172,1418,198,1909]" captionTargetId="figure-17@2.[155,1433,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Male habitus: a—dorsal view of a lectotype of Leptagrion andromache Hagen in Selys, 1876 and paratype´s labels (IRSNB); b—lateral view of L. andromache from Amapá state, Brazil; c—lateral view of holotype of Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (FAAL); d—Comparison between Leptagrion andromache and Leptagrion jeromei forewing pterostigma." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704350" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704350/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Fig. 1c</figureCitation>
). S1–2 dorsally dark brown, remainder pale brown; S3–5 light brown dorsally, pale brown laterally, S6–9 dark brown dorsally, pale greenish-brown laterally with black basal rings; anterior portion of S10 black dorsolaterally, remainder brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB7436D300655119C8EED83B3DC5C8F5" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100655119C8EED83B3DE8C83D" box="[199,395,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Anal appendages</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="33F02A5600655119C9B4D83B3E7AC83E" box="[413,537,331,358]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1377,1401]" captionTargetBox="[164,1423,192,1341]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[154,1433,181,1353]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Male Appendages: a—lateral view of a lectotype of Leptagrion andromache Hagen in Selys, 1876 (IRSNB); b—dorsal view (same specimen of a); c—lateral view of a paratype of Leptagrion jeromei spec. nov. (FAAL); d—dorsal view (same specimen of c)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5704354" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5704354/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Figs. 3c–d</figureCitation>
). Dark brown; subequal in length to S10; in lateral view, with a small, dorsal, blunt, medial projection; in dorsal view, distal tooth short, not reaching middle portion of cercus, with blunt tips directed anteromedially.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB7436D300655119C8EED8C73F7EC889" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,797,439,465]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Measurements. TL: 47, AL: 39.4; FW: 23; HW: 22.3.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB7436D300655119C8EED8AB3DF9C8AD" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,645]" box="[199,410,475,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100655119C8EED8AB3D7DC8AD" bold="true" box="[199,286,475,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB7436D300655119C8EED88E3C8DCBDD" blockId="3.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="99BFEAC100655119C8EED88E3D8BCB41" bold="true" box="[199,488,510,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
Variations in 
<typeStatus id="7470887100655119C943D88F3D81CB41" box="[362,482,511,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">paratypes</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Overall coloration of 
<specimenCount id="BDCDFD5A00655119CACCD88F3F15CB41" box="[741,886,511,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" type="generic" typeStatus="paratype">one paratype</specimenCount>
(collected 
<date id="DF75101300655119CBDCD88F383CCB42" box="[1013,1119,511,538]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" value="2006-01-11">11.i.2006</date>
) is paler, the light brown in the abdomen of the 
<typeStatus id="7470887100655119C95FDB533DBBCB65" box="[374,472,547,573]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">holotype</typeStatus>
is replaced by a light green and the black in the labrum, anteclypeus, postclypeus, antefrons and genae is replaced by blue. Size differences compatible with a species that breeds in phytotelmata (TL: 47–52).
</paragraph>
